item.title: Whitney Kae add a quote by Barbara Kingsolver
item.description: "Your dreams, what you hope for and all that, it's not separate from your life. It grows right up out of it. " -- Barbara Kingsolver

item.title: Whitney Kae add a quote by Mark Haddon
item.description: "Prime numbers are what is left when you have taken all the patterns away. I think prime numbers are like life. They are very logical but you could never work out the rules, even if you spent all your time thinking about them." -- Mark Haddon

item.title: Whitney Kae add a quote by Arthur Conan Doyle; Corrections And Editor Edgar W. Smith; Illustrators
item.description: "The world is full of obvious things which nobody by any chance ever observes." -- Arthur Conan Doyle; Corrections And Editor Edgar W. Smith; Illustrators

item.title: Whitney Kae add a quote by Theodor Herzl
item.description: "If you will it, it is no dream." -- Theodor Herzl
